http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/City-youth-convicted-in-terror-case/article14442032.ece

Obaid-ur-Rahman, who was among the 13 persons convicted by a special court in Bengaluru on Friday in a terror case, was a Hyderabad-based degree second year student when he was arrested by the Karnataka police in the last week of September, 2012.Initially, the Bengaluru police investigated the case. Intelligence officials then said Obaid-ur-Rahman and his associates, at the behest of their handlers from Saudi Arabia, targeted three corporators in Hyderabad. Later, the National Investigation Agency’s Hyderabad branch took over the investigation.